@startuml CompleteOrderLifecycle
title Complete Order Lifecycle

participant "Customer\nApp" as Customer
participant "API\nGateway" as Gateway
participant "Kitchen\nApp" as Kitchen
participant "Cashier\nApp" as Cashier
participant "Services" as Services

Customer -> Gateway: 1️⃣ POST /orders\n{source: WEB}
activate Gateway
Gateway -> Services: Service orchestration
activate Services
Services --> Gateway: Order{id, CREATED}
deactivate Services
Gateway --> Customer: HTTP 201
deactivate Gateway

Customer -> Gateway: 2️⃣ POST /orders/{id}/items\n{itemId, qty: 2}
activate Gateway
Gateway -> Services: Validate + Add
activate Services
Services --> Gateway: Item added
deactivate Services
Gateway --> Customer: HTTP 201
deactivate Gateway

Kitchen -> Gateway: 3️⃣ GET /orders/{id}/status
activate Gateway
Gateway -> Services: Query status
Services --> Gateway: Status: CREATED
deactivate Services
Gateway --> Kitchen: Show order
deactivate Gateway

Kitchen -> Gateway: 4️⃣ POST /orders/{id}/status\n{status: PREPARING}
activate Gateway
Gateway -> Services: Update status + Publish event
activate Services
Services --> Gateway: HTTP 201
deactivate Services
Gateway --> Kitchen: Status updated
deactivate Gateway

Kitchen -> Gateway: 5️⃣ POST /orders/{id}/status\n{status: READY}  
activate Gateway
Gateway -> Services: Update status + Publish event
Services --> Gateway: HTTP 201
deactivate Gateway

Cashier -> Gateway: 6️⃣ POST /orders/{id}/payments\n{method: CARD}
activate Gateway
Gateway -> Services: Process payment\nCreate Payment{with ID}
activate Services
Services --> Gateway: Payment{id, amount, SUCCEEDED}
deactivate Services
Gateway --> Cashier: HTTP 201
deactivate Gateway

Kitchen -> Gateway: 7️⃣ POST /orders/{id}/status\n{status: SERVED}
activate Gateway
Gateway -> Services: Update status
Services --> Gateway: HTTP 201
deactivate Gateway

note over Services
  Complete Flow Summary:
  - Order created (CREATED)
  - Items added (totalPrice calculated)
  - Status: PREPARING (event published)
  - Status: READY (event published)
  - Payment processed (Payment ID created)
  - Status: SERVED (complete)
end note
@enduml
